Defendant Robin Ann Flores in court with attorney Christian Eichenlaub for Anne M Jaspers.  Defendant Robin Ann Flores in custody.  David T. Malone appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
On motion of the State, Court ordered count 1 amended to Battery, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 940.19(1), a Misd.
AS TO COUNTS 1 AND 2  Defendant changes plea to NO CONTEST. Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights. Plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. 

AS TO COUNT 1: Defendant ordered to serve 9 months in the House of Correction concurrent to any other sentence with credit of 48 days time served, and with Huber Privileges for work and childcare.  
AS TO COUNT 2: Defendant ordered to serve 9 months in the House of Correction concurrent to any other sentence with credit of 48 days time served, and with Huber Privileges for work and childcare.  
AS TO BOTH COUNTS: Court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on probation for 24 months with the following conditions:
Alcohol and drug assessment and comply with any treatment deemed necessary by the department.
NO CONTACT ORDER REMAINS. 
Defendant to undergo a mental health assessment.  Defendant to attend Batterers Intervention. 
Court ordered defendant to pay all applicable court costs and surcharges by over the duration of probation or, if not paid, a civil judgment will be ordered.
